	"FriendlyName": "AFL Net Types",
	"Description": "Always-loaded home for AFL cross-cutting REPLICATED types (custom FGameplayAbilityTargetData subclasses and any USTRUCT sent over a GAS/net RPC). MUST stay a plain Default-phase runtime plugin -- NOT a GameFeature: GAS builds FNetSerializeScriptStructCache once, lazily, from the structs loaded at first ASC-globals access, and a struct in a late-loading GameFeature is absent/mis-indexed on one endpoint -> ServerSetReplicatedTargetData deserialize mismatch -> connection lost. Every networked weapon's net-types belong here, never in a GameFeature.",
	"Category": "AFL",
	"CreatedBy": "C12 AI Gaming",
